{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"06943d969e92db0d4c87cd30ad7a1a54","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the function returns `---\\n<yaml>---\\n<body>`. But `ExtractFrontmatter` looks for `\\n---` in the content (after stripping the opening `---\\n`). And `ExtractBody` looks for `\\n---\\n`. So:\n\nFor content `---\\nplanning_retry_count: 0\\nphase: planning\\n---\\n## Objective\\n`:\n- `ExtractFrontmatter` strips `---`, gets `\\nplanning_retry_count: 0\\nphase: planning\\n---\\n## Objective`\n- Strips leading `\\n`, gets `planning_retry_count: 0\\nphase: planning\\n---\\n## Objective`\n\n\n- Finds `\\n---` at `planning_retry_count: 0\\nphase: planning\\n` and extracts just the YAML frontmatter\n\nFor `ExtractBody`, it strips the opening `---` and leading newline, leaving `planning_retry_count: 0\\nphase: planning\\n---\\n## Objective`. Then it searches for `\\n---\\n` but only finds `\\n---` without the trailing newline, so it fails to extract the body. The issue is that the closing delimiter needs a newline after it for `ExtractBody` to work properly.\n\nIf I format the content as `---\\nplanning_retry_count: 0\\nphase: planning\\n---\\n## Objective\\n`, then `ExtractFrontmatter` would correctly find the YAML frontmatter by looking for `\\n---`, and `ExtractBody` would successfully locate `\\n---\\n` with the proper newline padding on both sides.\n\nThe fix is to modify the `onDiskFile` function to produce content with `---\\n` as the closing delimiter rather than just `---`, ensuring the newlines are in the right places for both extraction functions to work correctly.","signature":"59636a4855b5538978f34aa9d3edde1ac7b4e6c179d2145f36898d6db5ce017e"}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":92446,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":23387},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f5cbbde6-249d-