{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"06943fe94d45c790d59e9239263d7b9c","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"AH HA! There's the problem. When I have:\n```\nplanning_retry_count: null\nphase: planning\ntask_identifier: pr-123\n...\n## Objective\n```\n\nThe YAML parser sees `## Objective` and thinks `##` is an invalid key at line 11 because it's not `key: value` format. So the YAML parser FAILS and returns an empty map `{}`!\n\nThis explains everything:\n1. When `yaml.Unmarshal` fails, `fm` is an empty map\n2. `fm.Int(\"planning_retry_count\")` → `ok=false` → `count=0` (clamped)\n\n\n3. The modify closure tries to unmarshal the YAML content, but it fails because `## Objective` isn't valid YAML, leaving us with an empty map\n4. When we set `fm[\"planning_retry_count\"] = 1`, we're adding to that empty map, so marshaling produces `planning_retry_count: 1` without error\n5. Back in the test, unmarshaling the result gives us `fm` with just `planning_retry_count: 1`, and calling `Int(\"planning_retry_count\")` returns `1` successfully\n\nSo the issue is that the YAML parser can't handle the `## Objective` line as part of the frontmatter, but since we marshal it back out without that line, it works fine in the modify closure. The test expects to find `retry 1/3:` in the body, but the modify closure removed it when re-marshaling the frontmatter. the `resultBytes` are the bytes returned by the modify closure, which should have `planning_retry_count: 1` in the frontmatter. The body should contain `retry 1/3:`. So `fm.Int(\"planning_retry_count\")` should return `1`. But the test is failing with `Expected 0 to equal 1`! \n\nUNLESS the yaml.Unmarshal is failing in the test too. Let me check if `result.ExtractFrontmatter` can handle the content. The content format is:\n`---\\n<yaml>\\n---\\n<body>`\n\nAnd `ExtractFrontmatter` returns the YAML between `---` and `\\n---`. But the YAML itself contains `## Objective` which is NOT valid YAML! When we try to unmarshal this invalid YAML, it should fail and return an error, but I'm not checking for that error in the test.\n\nActually wait - when yaml.Unmarshal fails, the `fm` map might be partially populated or empty. The test expects `count = 1` but if unmarshal fails silently and leaves `fm` empty, then `fm.Int(...)` would return `0`. So the test failure suggests the unmarshal is failing but the error isn't being handled properly.\n\nThe issue is that when yaml.Unmarshal encounters an error on the `## Objective` line, it stops parsing and returns a partial or empty map, so `planning_retry_count` never gets set and the count remains 0 instead of 1. The issue is that YAML treats `## Objective` as an invalid mapping key since it lacks a colon, causing the parser to fail and leave the frontmatter map empty. This explains why the test sees count=0 instead of the expected value—the parsing error prevents the field from being populated at all.","signature":"fdb923c0a4e73d3edcd71bf5b4d6466900b417d4a1a2ad859ff4dd21b8add21d"}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":101172,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":23387},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f5cbbde6-249d-4959-8c10-2d095dee03df","uuid":"36c1150a-fa8d-41ae-94f9-a5a221de21dd"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"06943fe94d45c790d59e9239263d7b9c","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see the bug now! The YAML content in the test has `## Objective\\n\\nreview the PR\\n\\n## Progress\\n\\n- retry 1/3:...` which is NOT valid YAML. The `##` lines are YAML comments but then `## Objective` on its own line isn't valid key:value. This causes `yaml.Unmarshal` to fail, leaving an empty map, so `Int()` returns 0.\n\nI need to add a comment character (`#`) before section headers in the body, OR put them after valid YAML. Actually, the simplest fix is to just use content that doesn't have `##` section headers as standalone YAML-parsable content:\n"}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":101172,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":23387},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f5cbbde6-249d-4959-8c10-2d095dee03df","uuid":"48d61f1a-f6a3-4232-aad7-099dab77d5c9"}
